in crime. No matter what anyone says, the latest police statistics from May 2015 to May 2016—these are the latest statistics—show that every single measure except one, so nine out of the 10 crime categories that the police measure, actually went up.</p><p class="Interjection"><strong>Dr David Clark</strong>: Nine out of 10?</p><p class="ContinueSpeech"><strong>STUART NASH</strong>: Nine out of 10 went up. </p><p class="a">The Government cannot stand up and say that crime is falling, because the police statistics paint a different picture. What I believe the police need—what I absolutely believe the police need—is not more Tasers, not more guns, but more resources. The police need more police on the ground involved in community policing and more police in the stations solving crime, because the only way we are going to get crime numbers down and resolution numbers up is when we get our community policing working well and our traditional policing working well. Thank you.</p></div></body>
